summary:
Here is a clear and concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council, 
Noting the tense situation in the Middle East, 
Having considered the report of the Secretary-General on UNDOF, 
Expressing concern at violations of the Disengagement of Forces Agreement, 

1. Calls on parties to implement resolution 338 (1973); 
2. Calls on parties to cooperate with UNDOF operations and ensure security and access for UN personnel; 
3. Stresses parties' obligation to respect the 1974 Disengagement of Forces Agreement and calls for maximum restraint; 
4. Welcomes UNDOF's efforts to implement zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse; 
5. Notes progress in implementing recommendations on UNDOF's operational capacity; 
6. Renews UNDOF's mandate for six months, until 31 December 2012; 
7. Requests the Secretary-General to report on developments and measures taken to implement resolution 338.
